{"name": "pylint-per-file-ignores", "metadata": {"name": "pylint-per-file-ignores", "version": "1.3.2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/christopherpickering/pylint-per-file-ignores.git", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "A pylint plugin to ignore error codes per file.", "upload_time": 1695192299}, "documentation": ["# Pylint Per File Ignores \ud83d\ude32\n\nThis pylint plugin will enable per-file-ignores in your project!\n\n## Install\n\n```\n# w/ poetry\npoetry add --dev pylint-per-file-ignores\n\n# w/ pip\npip install pylint-per-file-ignores\n```\n\n## Add to Pylint Settings\n\n```toml\n[tool.pylint.MASTER]\nload-plugins=[\n    \"pylint_per_file_ignores\",\n    ...\n]\n```\n\n\n## Usage\n\nAdd list of patterns and codes you would like to ignore.\n\n### Using native pylint settings\n\nSection \"MESSAGES CONTROL\". Examples:\n\n```ini\n# setup.cfg\n\n[pylint.MESSAGES CONTROL]\nper-file-ignores =\n  /folder_1/:missing-function-docstring,W0621,W0240,C0115\n  file.py:C0116,E0001\n```\n\n```toml\n# pyproject.toml\n\n[tool.pylint.'MESSAGES CONTROL']\nper-file-ignores = [\n    \"/folder_1/:missing-function-docstring,W0621,W0240,C0115\",\n    \"file.py:C0116,E0001\"\n]\n```\n\n### Using custom `pyproject.toml` section\n\nFor backwards compatibility only. Example:\n\n```toml\n[tool.pylint-per-file-ignores]\n\"/folder_1/\"=\"missing-function-docstring,W0621,W0240,C0115\"\n\"file.py\"=\"C0116,E0001\"\n```\n\n## Thanks\n\nTo pylint :) And the plugin `pylint-django` who produced most of the complex code.\n\n## Contributing\n\nThis repo uses commitizen and semantic release. Please commit using `npm run commit` .\n"], "modules": [{"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.find_pyproject", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "src", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Optional", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Optional", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "Path", "xref": {"fqname": "pathlib.Path", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Search upstream for a pyproject.toml file."]}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.get_checker_by_msg", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "msg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.get_message_definitions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message_id_or_symbol", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Lookup that onverts a symbol or message string into a unified message."]}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.augment_all_visit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message_id_or_symbol", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "augmentation", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Augmenting a visit enables additional errors to be raised (although that case is\nbetter served using a new checker) or to suppress all warnings in certain\ncircumstances.\nAugmenting functions should accept a 'chain' function, which runs the checker\nmethod and possibly any other augmentations, and secondly an Astroid node.\n\"chain()\" can be called at any point to trigger the continuation of other\nchecks, or not at all to prevent any further checking."]}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.augment_add_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message_id_or_symbol", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test_func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Rather than augmenting all visit method,\nthis override the checker.add_message method\nto cover all possible source of warnings.\n@returns True if checker.add_message method override is successful."]}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.disable_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "message_id", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "test_func", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["This wrapper allows the suppression of a message if the supplied test function\nreturns True."]}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.register", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": {"name": "PyLinter", "xref": {"fqname": "pylint.lint.PyLinter", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.load_configuration", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "linter", "type": {"name": "PyLinter", "xref": {"fqname": "pylint.lint.PyLinter", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.Suppress", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.Suppress.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "linter", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.Suppress.__enter__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "pylint_per_file_ignores.Suppress.add_message", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "*args", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs"